Walking School Bus students.... take a look at our schedule! This schedule will run every day we have in-person school, beginning on the first day of school, August 24th. We are using the same routes before and after school.

We ask that students please be at their pick-up spot at the designated time! The Walking School bus will not wait, as we need to stay on schedule. If it's rainy, there will be no walking school bus that day. Parents are encouraged to have a plan for inclement weather days.

If you have questions or would like more information, please email walkingschoolbus@mflmm.k12.ia.us.

post_text:
A message from Superintendent Dr. Dale Crozier:

Throughout this pandemic, we have carefully considered the health, safety, and social and emotional needs of our students and staff in all decisions. Below is MFL MarMac's Return To Learn plan as it stands today. This document represents a summarization of work completed by the R2L committee, and they are to be commended. We all worked together, but that was expected as we always work together here at MFL MarMac.

The plan is to come back physically on August 24 (per Governor’s orders) unless we are told that we cannot do so. As long as it is safe, we will physically be in school as much as we can Please remember this document is fluid and tentative and subject to change. We have conducted numerous needs assessments throughout our planning process. Further assessments will conducted as we continue in this process. Please know that we are here for you and we are all in this together.

#mflmarmaccommUNITY, #mflmarmacbulldogs

https://bit.ly/MFLMMR2L

post_text: Thank you to everyone who helped us celebrate our 2020 graduates!
shared_text:
North Iowa Times
July 17 at 11:32 AM ·

MFL MarMac held an in-person diploma ceremony on July 10, celebrating the Class of 2020. The event was held on the football field, where families (in groups of no more than 10) and graduates were able to space out. Short but sweet, the ceremony lasted just over a half-hour and included musical performances and a few words from high school principal Larry Meyer. The seniors then took to the stage, picking up their own diplomas and flowers, as well as flipping their own tassels, in an effort to limit physical contact.

post_text: A nice video showcasing the Class of 2020! Thanks NIT!
shared_text:
North Iowa Times
May 15 at 3:34 PM ·

In an interview with the North Iowa Times-Clayton County Register, MFL MarMac salutatorian Eli Johnson referenced the success the senior class has experienced in not just academics, but sports, fine arts, FFA and other activities.

“That reflects on the people in the class—their attitudes and the work they put in,” said Eli. “There are a lot of very good students in this class, and that’s translated into a lot of different areas. It will add to success later.”

We couldn't agree more. It was a pleasure to cover these happy moments and highlight the fun, hardworking and kind students in the class of 2020. Congratulations on your graduation and best wishes in all your future endeavors!

To all parents/guardians of children entering 9th grade for the school year 2020-2021:

A proof of Dental Screening is required by the State of Iowa one year prior to and no later than 4 months after the start date of the 2020-2021 school year (Aug. 2019 - Dec. 2020). If your child has already received a dental screening, please contact the provider and have them complete a Dental Screening Form (link below) and return it to the school. If your child has not been evaluated by a dental health professional please make arrangements to do so. For further questions or concerns, please feel free to contact the MFL MarMac Nursing Staff at 563-539-2032 or via email at sara.kelly@mflmm.k12.ia.us or donna.krambeer@mflmm.k12.ia.us.

We are #BulldogProud today as the MFL MarMac Student Council saw a need and chose to help!

The council took a vote and unanimously decided to donate $1,000 from their High School Student Council Fund to the Clayton County Food Shelf. As one member said, "Especially in this time of unknowns, the student council would do anything to assist those around us. I am so grateful to be in such a giving group."

We are grateful for these students and their giving spirit! #MFLMarMacCommUNITY

post_text: Congrats Kira Rieck!
shared_text:
Monona FFA
April 27 at 1:56 PM ·

For the first time in school history, MFL MarMac has a Borlaug Scholar! Kira Rieck participated in the virtual Iowa Youth Institute today. She wrote a paper about the arising conflict within the heart of Uganda and defended her solution during a student roundtable discussion.

She also attended an Immersion Discussion hosted by ISU Associate Dean, Dr. David Acker. She learned about her future major, Global Resource Systems, and career of becoming a hunger fighter.

Kira received a $500 scholarship to the College of Agriculture at Iowa State, where she will attend in the fall. We are proud of her for being the first student to represent our school at this amazing event. Congratulations!

post_text:
MFL Mar Mac and other schools around the state came together to “Light Up Iowa” by lighting up our stadiums at 8:00 pm each Friday night. At 8:00 weekly on Friday night we will join together and turn on the lights of our stadiums and leave them on for one minute for each day we have been out of school.

April 10 15 minutes
April 17 20 minutes
April 24 25 minutes

We took this opportunity to light up the night and let our community and students know that we miss them and look forward to having them back in our stadiums with the lights on and our community back together.

#lightupIA

post_text:
Parents and Guardians of Students at the McGregor Center:
Teachers at MFL MarMac McGregor Center have been working hard and will continue to do so as they reach out to students during this difficult pandemic time. Many parents have already made arrangements to pick up an IPAD from the McGregor Center in order to keep their child connected and working on the various optional activities given by our teachers. If you did not reach out to acquire an IPAD and would still like one, please email Mrs. Mueller (denise.mueller@mflmm.k12.ia.us) and arrange a pick up time. Also, if for any reason you do not wish to have your son or daughter zoom or use google hangouts with their teacher or class, please let me know. Again, feel free to contact me with any questions or concerns as we navigate through this difficult time.Make sure your son or daughter is checking their gmail on a daily basis as this is the method most teachers will be using to connect with students.Stay safe and healthy and know that I miss all of my students. Mrs. Mueller

post_text: Shout-Out to Speech today!
shared_text:
MFL MarMac Speech Team
March 30 at 9:41 AM ·

TODAY, March 30 would have been the day for the All-State Individual Speech Festival at UNI. Our congratulations to our MFL MarMac speech participants who were chosen for these exceptional honors! We wish you could have had the experience of attending the festival, but we are very proud of all your accomplishments this year in Speech!

Congrats to Max Koeller for double recognition in both the Acting and Solo Musical Theater categories! Congrats to Dika Putri for Poetry, Jaxton Schroeder for Radio News Broadcasting, Nick Stavroplus for Spontaneous Speaking, and Jonah Wille for Storytelling!

post_text: Thank you to so many of you who generously offered up your collection of grocery bags today for our Meal Site program, as well as those kiddos who showed up with their backpacks! Unfortunately we are unable to accept used bags at this time in an effort to avoid contamination. Casino Queen came to our rescue today with a large bundle just before we set out to do deliveries and Bruns & James Insurance let us know that they have a shipment headed our way too. Other generous businesses and individuals have since stepped forward and offered their supplies as well. Thank you, thank you, thank you! We are so blessed to have such a thoughtful and generous community! 💙💛💙💛 #bulldogsunited

shared_text:
MFL MarMac Speech Team
March 13 at 8:27 PM ·

We are hosting our own State Individual Speech Contest tomorrow at MFL MarMac High School! Come watch the 20 MFL MarMac and 9 Lansing Kee students who advanced from the district contests and are vying for All-State honors.

[Note: the IHSSA approved having districts hire their own certified judges when the larger state speech contest had to be cancelled.]

So...come out and watch some awesome performances. You’ll see a variety including solo musical theater, poetry/prose, acting, improvisation, after-dinner
speaking, radio news broadcasting, and more!

Performances begin at 8:30 am in the HS Library. The public is welcome!

post_text: Members from McGregor’s Hook & Ladder and the Clayton County Sheriff’s Office recently joined the students in the McGregor Center for lunch and time on the ski slopes. The LEO/EMS campaign, that has been organized by the Middle School Stu Crew, made these relationship-building experiences possible! We welcome more members from the local LEO/EMS communities to come join us for lunch, field trips, and other school activities and events so we can continue to raise awareness and create trusting relationships between our youth and our local LEO/EMS personnel.

post_text: What a great experience with Kevin Honeycutt. Kevin was a guest speaker at MFL MarMac on February 13th and 14th. Kevin brought life experiences and a sense of humor into his mission to help teachers prepare students for 21st century learning. He gave the staff tools and tactics to rejuvenate their practice. He also spoke about how to connect with lost learners and how to get them back on a path to success. Check him out on YouTube or Twitter.
